    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Is there any reason to encode `[` and `]` in URLs? As far as I know, that's how HTML5 forms that have arrays are sent and they are not encoded. Like `name[0]=Actor1&name[1]=Actor2`. I think not encoding these 2 characters will provide a more readable URL and keep the compatibility.",
